         <abstract>
            <p>Let α denote a real algebraic number that is a root of a polynomial f(x) ∈ Z[ x ]. The purpose of this paper is to state an algorithm for finding the simple continued fraction expansion of α. Furthermore, an application of the algorithm to sign determination in real algebraic number fields is given.</p>
          </abstract>
